The '''Karashima clan''' (辛嶋氏) was an ancient {{ill|Japanese clans|ja|日本の氏族|12=draft}}. The clan served as shrine families of {{ill|Usa Shrine|ja|宇佐八幡宮|12=draft}}. The name is also written as '''Karashima''' or '''Kanashima'''. The {{ill|kabane|ja|カバネ|12=draft}} title was {{ill|Suguri|ja|村主|12=draft}}.

== Origin ==

The Karashima clan is generally considered to be a {{ill|Toraijin|ja|渡来系氏族|12=draft}}.<ref name="inuma" /> The genealogical records of the Karashima clan claim descent from {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素戔嗚尊|12=draft}} through his son {{ill|Itakeru-no-Mikoto|ja|五十猛神|12=draft}}, further suggesting a migrant origin.<ref name="inuma" />

== Overview ==

The Karashima clan produced female shrine priests ({{ill|negimi|ja|禰宜|12=draft}}) who served at {{ill|Usa Shrine|ja|宇佐神宮|12=draft}} during the {{ill|Asuka period|ja|飛鳥時代|12=draft}} and {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|12=draft}}. 

Originally, they served as priests and priestesses at {{ill|Komo Shrine|ja|薦神社|12=draft}} (in present-day {{ill|Nakatsu, Ōita|ja|中津市|12=draft}}). After receiving an oracle from the {{ill|Hachiman deity|ja|八幡神|12=draft}}, they, along with {{ill|Ōgami Hiyoshi|ja|大神比義|12=draft}}, established a shrine that became the forerunner of Usa Shrine.

According to the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft}} (Volume 27, entry for November in the 10th year of {{ill|Emperor Tenji|ja|天智天皇|12=draft}} [671 CE]), {{ill|Kanashima Saba|ja|韓嶋裟婆|12=draft}} and three others reported that {{ill|Tang China|ja|唐|12=draft}} and {{ill|Silla|ja|新羅|12=draft}} were preparing to invade Japan.<ref>''Nihon Shoki,'' entry for Emperor Tenji, 10th year, 11th month.</ref>

Following the {{ill|Hayato Rebellion|ja|隼人の反乱|12=draft}} in the 4th year of {{ill|Yōrō|ja|養老|12=draft}} (720 CE), residents of {{ill|Buzen Province|ja|豊前国|12=draft}} were relocated to {{ill|Ōsumi Province|ja|大隅国|12=draft}}. It is speculated that the Karashima clan may have a connection to {{ill|Kankoku-uzumine Shrine|ja|韓国宇豆峰神社|12=draft}}, which enshrines {{ill|Itakeru-no-Mikoto|ja|五十猛命|12=draft}}.<ref name="inuma" />

During the {{ill|Jingō-keiun|ja|神護景雲|12=draft}} era (769 CE), during the {{ill|Usa Hachiman Oracle Incident|ja|宇佐八幡宮神託事件|12=draft}}, the priestess {{ill|Karashima no Suguri Yosome|ja|辛嶋勝与曽女|12=draft}} received an oracle from the Hachiman deity and refused twice to hear the imperial decree read by {{ill|Wake no Kiyomaro|ja|和気清麻呂|12=draft}}, the envoy of {{ill|Empress Shōtoku|ja|称徳天皇|12=draft}}.<ref name="inuma" />

