The '''Karashima clan''' (辛嶋氏) was an ancient {{ill|Japanese clans|ja|日本の氏族|12=draft|12=draft}}. The clan served as shrine families of {{ill|Usa Shrine|ja|宇佐八幡宮|12=draft|12=draft}}. The name is also written as '''Karashima''' or '''Kanashima'''. The {{ill|kabane|ja|カバネ|12=draft|12=draft}} title was {{ill|Suguri|ja|村主|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== Origin ==

The Karashima clan is generally considered to be a {{ill|Toraijin|ja|渡来系氏族|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref name="inuma" /> The genealogical records of the Karashima clan claim descent from {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素戔嗚尊|12=draft|12=draft}} through his son {{ill|Itakeru-no-Mikoto|ja|五十猛神|12=draft|12=draft}}, further suggesting a migrant origin.<ref name="inuma" />

