The '''Karashima clan''' (辛嶋氏) was an ancient {{ill|Japanese clans|ja|日本の氏族|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese clans|qq=}}. The clan served as shrine families of {{ill|Usa Shrine|ja|宇佐八幡宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usa Shrine|qq=}}. The name is also written as '''Karashima''' or '''Kanashima'''. The {{ill|kabane|ja|カバネ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/kabane|qq=}} title was {{ill|Suguri|ja|村主|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suguri|qq=}}.

== Origin ==

The Karashima clan is generally considered to be a {{ill|Toraijin|ja|渡来系氏族|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toraijin|qq=}}.<ref name="inuma" /> The genealogical records of the Karashima clan claim descent from {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素戔嗚尊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=}} through his son {{ill|Itakeru-no-Mikoto|ja|五十猛神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Itakeru-no-Mikoto|qq=}}, further suggesting a migrant origin.<ref name="inuma" />

