== Overview ==

The Karashima clan produced female shrine priests ({{ill|negimi|ja|禰宜|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/negimi|qq=}}) who served at {{ill|Usa Shrine|ja|宇佐神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usa Shrine|qq=}} during the {{ill|Asuka period|ja|飛鳥時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asuka period|qq=}} and {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara period|qq=}}. 

Originally, they served as priests and priestesses at {{ill|Komo Shrine|ja|薦神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Komo Shrine|qq=}} (in present-day {{ill|Nakatsu, Ōita|ja|中津市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakatsu, Ōita|qq=}}). After receiving an oracle from the {{ill|Hachiman deity|ja|八幡神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman deity|qq=}}, they, along with {{ill|Ōgami Hiyoshi|ja|大神比義|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōgami Hiyoshi|qq=}}, established a shrine that became the forerunner of Usa Shrine.

According to the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Shoki|qq=}} (Volume 27, entry for November in the 10th year of {{ill|Emperor Tenji|ja|天智天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenji|qq=}} [671 CE]), {{ill|Kanashima Saba|ja|韓嶋裟婆|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanashima Saba|qq=}} and three others reported that {{ill|Tang China|ja|唐|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tang China|qq=}} and {{ill|Silla|ja|新羅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Silla|qq=}} were preparing to invade Japan.<ref>''Nihon Shoki,'' entry for Emperor Tenji, 10th year, 11th month.</ref>

Following the {{ill|Hayato Rebellion|ja|隼人の反乱|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hayato Rebellion|qq=}} in the 4th year of {{ill|Yōrō|ja|養老|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yōrō|qq=}} (720 CE), residents of {{ill|Buzen Province|ja|豊前国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Buzen Province|qq=}} were relocated to {{ill|Ōsumi Province|ja|大隅国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōsumi Province|qq=}}. It is speculated that the Karashima clan may have a connection to {{ill|Kankoku-uzumine Shrine|ja|韓国宇豆峰神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kankoku-uzumine Shrine|qq=}}, which enshrines {{ill|Isotakeru-no-Mikoto|lt=Isotakeru-no-Mikoto|lt=Itakeru-no-Mikoto|ja|五十猛命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Itakeru-no-Mikoto|qq=}}.<ref name="inuma" />

During the {{ill|Jingō-keiun|ja|神護景雲|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jingō-keiun|qq=}} era (769 CE), during the {{ill|Usa Hachiman Oracle Incident|ja|宇佐八幡宮神託事件|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usa Hachiman Oracle Incident|qq=}}, the priestess {{ill|Karashima no Suguri Yosome|ja|辛嶋勝与曽女|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karashima no Suguri Yosome|qq=}} received an oracle from the Hachiman deity and refused twice to hear the imperial decree read by {{ill|Wake no Kiyomaro|ja|和気清麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wake no Kiyomaro|qq=}}, the envoy of {{ill|Empress Shōtoku|ja|称徳天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Empress Shōtoku|qq=}}.<ref name="inuma" />

