Originally, they served as priests and priestesses at {{ill|Komo Shrine (Oita)|lt=Komo Shrine (Oita)|lt=Komo Shrine|ja|薦神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Komo Shrine|qq=}} (in present-day {{ill|Nakatsu, Ōita|ja|中津市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakatsu, Ōita|qq=}}). After receiving an oracle from the {{ill|Hachiman deity|ja|八幡神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman deity|qq=}}, they, along with {{ill|Ōgami Hiyoshi|ja|大神比義|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōgami Hiyoshi|qq=}}, established a shrine that became the forerunner of Usa Shrine.

