== Examination ==
Records hint at the presence of {{ill|Wa people|ja|倭人|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wa people|qq=}} in {{ill|Baekje|ja|百済|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Baekje|qq=}} under Tang's {{ill|Ungjin Commandery|ja|熊津都督府|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ungjin Commandery|qq=}}, including figures like {{ill|Nihora|ja|日羅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihora|qq=}}. These accounts suggest interactions between local Wa people and Tang administration post-{{ill|Battle of Baekgang|ja|白村江の戦い|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Battle of Baekgang|qq=}}.<ref name="kondo">{{Cite book|和書|author=Kondo Koichi|date=2021-12-15|title=Post-Baekgang Diplomacy of Tang's Ungjin Commandery|series=Jinbun x Shakai 1 (4)|publisher=Jinbun x Shakai Editorial Board|pages=30-33}}</ref> Further analysis aligns the Karashima clan's activities with these events.

