== Examination ==
Records hint at the presence of [[:en:Wajin (ancient people)|Wa people]] in [[:en:Baekje|Baekje]] under Tang's [[:en:Ungjin Commandery|Ungjin Commandery]], including figures like {{ill|Nihora|ja|日羅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihora|qq=|1=Nichira|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11510262}}. These accounts suggest interactions between local Wa people and Tang administration post-[[:en:Battle of Baekgang|Battle of Baekgang]].<ref name="kondo">{{Cite book|和書|author=Kondo Koichi|date=2021-12-15|title=Post-Baekgang Diplomacy of Tang's Ungjin Commandery|series=Jinbun x Shakai 1 (4)|publisher=Jinbun x Shakai Editorial Board|pages=30-33}}</ref> Further analysis aligns the Karashima clan's activities with these events.

