The '''Karashima clan''' (辛嶋氏) was an ancient {{ill|Japanese clans|ja|日本の氏族|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese clans|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. The clan served as shrine families of {{ill|Usa Jingū|lt=Usa Jingū|lt=Usa Shrine|ja|宇佐八幡宮|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usa Shrine|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 宇佐神宮}}. The name is also written as '''Karashima''' or '''Kanashima'''. The {{ill|Kabane|en|Kabane|qid=Q1664099|lt=kabane|1=Kabane}} title was {{ill|Suguri|ja|村主|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suguri|1=Q11522959|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11522959}}.

== Origin ==

The Karashima clan is generally considered to be a {{ill|Toraijin|ja|渡来系氏族|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toraijin|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.<ref name="inuma" /> The genealogical records of the Karashima clan claim descent from {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素戔嗚尊|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to スサノオ}} through his son {{ill|Isotakeru-no-Mikoto|qid=Q10881556|lt=Isotakeru-no-Mikoto|lt=Itakeru-no-Mikoto|ja|五十猛神|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Itakeru-no-Mikoto|qq=|1=Isotakeru-no-Mikoto}}, further suggesting a migrant origin.<ref name="inuma" />

== Overview ==

The Karashima clan produced female shrine priests ({{ill|negimi|ja|禰宜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/negimi|1=Negi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11594490}}) who served at {{ill|Usa Jingū|en|Usa Jingū|qid=Q715632|lt=Usa Shrine|1=Usa Jingū}} during the {{ill|Asuka period|en|Asuka period|qid=Q210688|lt=Asuka period|1=Asuka period}} and {{ill|Nara period|en|Nara period|qid=Q189178|lt=Nara period|1=Nara period}}. 

Originally, they served as priests and priestesses at {{ill|Komo Shrine (Oita)|lt=Komo Shrine (Oita)|lt=Komo Shrine|ja|薦神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Komo Shrine|qq=}} (in present-day {{ill|Nakatsu, Ōita|en|Nakatsu, Ōita|qid=Q861221|lt=Nakatsu, Ōita|1=Nakatsu, Ōita}}). After receiving an oracle from the {{ill|Hachiman|en|Hachiman|qid=Q261637|lt=Hachiman deity|1=Hachiman}}, they, along with {{ill|Ōgami Hiyoshi|ja|大神比義|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōgami Hiyoshi|1=Ōga no Higi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q119922506}}, established a shrine that became the forerunner of Usa Shrine.

According to the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|en|Nihon Shoki|qid=Q813935|lt=Nihon Shoki|1=Nihon Shoki}} (Volume 27, entry for November in the 10th year of {{ill|Emperor Tenji|en|Emperor Tenji|qid=Q314802|lt=Emperor Tenji|1=Emperor Tenji}} [671 CE]), {{ill|Kanashima Saba|ja|韓嶋裟婆|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanashima Saba|1=Q58420115|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q58420115}} and three others reported that {{ill|Tang dynasty|en|Tang dynasty|qid=Q9683|lt=Tang China|1=Tang dynasty}} and {{ill|Silla|en|Silla|qid=Q28456|lt=Silla|1=Silla}} were preparing to invade Japan.<ref>''Nihon Shoki,'' entry for Emperor Tenji, 10th year, 11th month.</ref>

Following the {{ill|Hayato rebellion|en|Hayato rebellion|qid=Q11659098|lt=Hayato Rebellion|1=Hayato rebellion}} in the 4th year of {{ill|Yōrō|en|Yōrō|qid=Q1373061|lt=Yōrō|1=Yōrō}} (720 CE), residents of {{ill|Buzen Province|en|Buzen Province|qid=Q1047134|lt=Buzen Province|1=Buzen Province}} were relocated to {{ill|Ōsumi Province|en|Ōsumi Province|qid=Q981002|lt=Ōsumi Province|1=Ōsumi Province}}. It is speculated that the Karashima clan may have a connection to {{ill|Kankoku-uzumine Shrine|ja|韓国宇豆峰神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kankoku-uzumine Shrine|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, which enshrines {{ill|Isotakeru-no-Mikoto|qid=Q10881556|lt=Isotakeru-no-Mikoto|lt=Itakeru-no-Mikoto|ja|五十猛命|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Itakeru-no-Mikoto|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 五十猛神|1=Isotakeru-no-Mikoto|2=ja|3=五十猛神|4=zh|5=五十猛神}}.<ref name="inuma" />

During the {{ill|Jingo-keiun|en|Jingo-keiun|qid=Q1373049|lt=Jingō-keiun|1=Jingo-keiun}} era (769 CE), during the {{ill|Usa Hachiman Oracle Incident|ja|宇佐八幡宮神託事件|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usa Hachiman Oracle Incident|1=Dōkyō Incident|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11449036}}, the priestess {{ill|Karashima no Suguri Yosome|ja|辛嶋勝与曽女|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karashima no Suguri Yosome|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} received an oracle from the Hachiman deity and refused twice to hear the imperial decree read by {{ill|Wake no Kiyomaro|en|Wake no Kiyomaro|qid=Q7961005|lt=Wake no Kiyomaro|1=Wake no Kiyomaro}}, the envoy of {{ill|Empress Shōtoku|ja|称徳天皇|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Empress Shōtoku|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 孝謙天皇|1=Empress Kōken|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q232955}}.<ref name="inuma" />

